cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about training sparse neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on image classification tasks (cs.CV) and uses ResNet-50 and MobileNet v1 and v2 architectures. The method proposed in the paper involves updating the topology of the network during training, which is a technique commonly used in neural architecture search (cs.NE) and can be seen as a form of automated machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also applies the method to recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.DS).
